.B snapm
.CMD_SNAPSET_DIFF
.br
Compare two snapshot sets, or a snapshot set and the running system.
.IP
Calculates the differences between the \fBfrom\fP and \fBto\fP targets. Targets
may be specified as a snapshot set name, or the special character \fB.\fP to
represent the currently running system (root file system).
.IP
The output format is controlled by \fB--output-format\fP. The \fBtree\fP
format provides a hierarchical view of changes, while \fBdiff\fP provides
standard unified diff output for modified content: see \fBOutput Formats\fP for
a full description of the available formats. Multiple output formats may be
specified by repeating the \fB--output-format\fP argument with the required
formats. The default format if no \fB--output-format\fP is specified is
\fBtree\fP.
.IP
File comparisons can be tuned to ignore specific attributes (timestamps,
permissions, ownership) or to filter based on file patterns and sizes.
.IP
By default the results of diff computations are stored in an on-disk cache.
The default cache expiry time is 900 seconds (15 minutes). Cache behaviour can
be controlled with the \fB--cache-mode\fP and \fB--cache-expires\fP options.
.IP
.B Output Formats
paths, full, short, json, diff, summary, tree
.IP
The \fB--output-format\fP option accepts the following values:
.IP
.B \[bu] paths
A simple list of changed paths, one per line.
.IP
.B \[bu] full
Detailed change information including file attributes (mode, user, group, size,
time).
.IP
.B \[bu] short
Abbreviated change description (path, difference type and summary).
.IP
.B \[bu] json
Change data formatted as a JSON object.
.IP
.B \[bu] diff
Standard unified diff output of file content changes.
.IP
.B \[bu] summary
A brief summary of the count of different change types.
.IP
.B \[bu] tree
(Default) A hierarchical tree view of changes, using prefixes to indicate
status.
.IP
.B Tree Output Legend
.IP
The \fBtree\fP output format uses the following prefixes to indicate file status:
.IP
.B \[bu] [+]
Path added (green)
.IP
.B \[bu] [-]
Path removed (red)
.IP
.B \[bu] [*]
Path modified (yellow)
.IP
.B \[bu] [<]
Path moved from (cyan)
.IP
.B \[bu] [>]
Path moved to (cyan)
.IP
.B \[bu] [!]
Path file type changed (blue)
.
