.SH JSON OUTPUT
.
All reporting commands can optionally generate output in JSON notation by
using the \fB--json\fP argument. The output is a JSON object containing a
key for the object type (\fISnapsets\fP, \fISnapshots\fP, \fIPlugins\fP, or
\fISchedules\fP) that contains a JSON array of objects of the specified type.
.P
Reporting commands use JSON key names derived from the report field names. For
\fIlist\fP reports the JSON keys are always prefixed with the object type to
avoid collisions (e.g., \fIsnapset_name\fP). The \fB-o\fP/\fB--options\fP and
\fB-O\fP/\fB--sort\fP arguments accept those report field names (prefixes are
optional unless required to disambiguate).
.P
Selection and sorting is controlled with \fB--options\fP and \fB--sort\fP as
usual:
.P
.EX
# snapm snapset list --json -o+snapset_uuid --sort snapset_time
{
    "Snapsets": [
        {
            "snapset_name": "before-upgrade",
            "snapset_time": "2025-09-08 18:43:57",
            "snapset_nr_snapshots": 2,
            "snapset_status": "Active",
            "snapset_sources": [
                "/",
                "/var"
            ],
            "snapset_uuid": "6330328b-a9d0-5b41-ac96-53b371449965"
        },
        {
            "snapset_name": "backup",
            "snapset_time": "2025-09-09 17:12:21",
            "snapset_nr_snapshots": 3,
            "snapset_status": "Inactive",
            "snapset_sources": [
                "/",
                "/home",
                "/var"
            ],
            "snapset_uuid": "efa8a09d-cf9c-500b-ad68-32c4a0e159b4"
        }
    ]
}
.EE
.PP
The \fBcreate\fP, \fBcreate-scheduled\fP, and \fBshow\fP subcommands also
support optional JSON notation using the \fB--json\fP argument. This includes
the \fBsnapset\fP, \fBsnapshot\fP, and \fBschedule\fP \fBshow\fP subcommands:
.PP
.EX
# snapm snapset show --json before-upgrade
[
    {
        "SnapsetName": "before-upgrade",
        "Sources": [
            "/",
            "/home",
            "/var"
       ],
        "MountPoints": [
            "/",
            "/home",
            "/var"
        ],
        "Devices": [],
        "NrSnapshots": 3,
        "Timestamp": 1755915019,
        "Time": "2025-08-23 03:10:19",
        "UUID": "d9b63a58-333b-517a-b38d-7cc818040fab",
        "Status": "Active",
        "Categories": [
            "yearly",
            "monthly",
            "daily",
            "hourly"
        ],
        "Autoactivate": true,
        "Bootable": true,
        "BootEntries": {
            "SnapshotEntry": "61cb664",
            "RevertEntry": "74c1cf2"
        }
    }
]
.EE
.P
The JSON format produced by the \fBcreate\fP and \fBshow\fP commands uses JSON
key names that reflect the property names used in the normal \fBshow\fP
command output. The output is a JSON array containing objects of the specified
type.
.P
When boot entries are defined for a snapshot set the resulting JSON will
include a \fIBootEntries\fP object giving the corresponding \fBboom\fP
\fIboot_id\fP values.
.P
The \fBcreate\fP commands output a single JSON object of the corresponding
type. The \fBshow\fP commands produce a JSON array containing the selected
objects.
